text: Maries County Jail and Sheriff's House, also known as the Old Jail Museum, is a historic jail and sheriff's residence located in Vienna, Maries County, Missouri. It was built between 1856 and 1858, and is a two-story rectangular building, constructed of rough-cut native limestone ashlar blocks. It was moved to its present location in 1959, where it is now used as a museum. (includes 16 photographs from 2001) It was added to the National Register of Historic Places in 2002. ==References== Category:History museums in Missouri Category:Government buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Missouri Category:Government buildings completed in 1858 Category:Buildings and structures in Maries County, Missouri Category:National Register of Historic Places in Maries County, Missouri
